ğŸ’» Installation (macOS DMG)

If you downloaded the Blossom Browser from the official site, macOS may prevent it from opening because itâ€™s unsigned.
To run it safely:

1ï¸âƒ£ Remove quarantine from the DMG

xattr -d com.apple.quarantine /path/to/blossom_arm64.dmg

2ï¸âƒ£ Mount the DMG

hdiutil attach /path/to/blossom_arm64.dmg

3ï¸âƒ£ Open the mounted volume

Drag Blossom.app into your Applications folder.

4ï¸âƒ£ Remove quarantine from the installed app

xattr -d com.apple.quarantine /Applications/"Blossom.app"

If you still get a warning, right-click â†’ Open once; macOS will then trust the app.

